data.chText: 尸体；（尤指人的）死尸，尸首
data.enText: a dead body, especially of a human

data.chText: （使戏剧演员因忘记台词或止不住笑而）演出僵住
data.enText: (in the theatre) to suddenly be unable to act, because you have forgotten your words or are laughing; to cause sb to do this

simple_means.memory_skill: corp 身体；团体 + se → 身体〔四分五裂〕→ 尸体

means: (使戏剧演员因忘记台词或止不住笑而)演出僵住

tr: the dead body of a human being
example: the cadaver was intended for dissection
the end of the police search was the discovery of a corpse
the murderer confessed that he threw the stiff in the river
honor comes to bless the turf that wraps their clay

value.def: A corpse is a dead body, especially the body of a human being.
